      "id": "PopularPost262125",
      "post_content": "IMHO this cards oracle text is wrong as this is ruled to be either life loss or gain depending what the players life was before this resolves. So it should read:  \n  \n![7](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=7&type=symbol)![White](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=W&type=symbol)![White](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=W&type=symbol)  \nSorcery  \n  \nTarget player gains or loses life so that their(1) life total becomes 20.  \n  \n  \n(1) 'Their' is acceptable singular third posessive form when gender is unknown. I hate the artificial 'his or her'.",
